1
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:36,911
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

2
00:00:49,090 --> 00:00:51,217
A beautiful love story always begins

3
00:00:51,384 --> 00:00:55,012
with a dramatic, fateful encounter.

4
00:00:55,096 --> 00:00:57,765
- Keep going!
- Let's go!

5
00:00:59,141 --> 00:01:01,310
But singles these days

6
00:01:01,811 --> 00:01:05,648
don't wait around for fate
to find love for them.

7
00:01:06,524 --> 00:01:08,025
REBOUND SIGNAL

8
00:01:08,859 --> 00:01:10,778
They choose their partners
however they like

9
00:01:11,279 --> 00:01:14,490
and decide
when to begin and end a relationship.

10
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:21,914
Everyone leads their own lives
in this generation

11
00:01:22,748 --> 00:01:25,084
and I'm also looking for my love.

12
00:01:34,552 --> 00:01:36,387
Are you waiting for your blind date?

13
00:01:37,096 --> 00:01:38,681
Yes, I am.

14
00:01:39,223 --> 00:01:40,349
I see.

15
00:01:41,475 --> 00:01:43,227
Hello, I'm Song Tae-seop.

16
00:01:44,604 --> 00:01:46,188
Nice to meet you, I'm Lee Ui-yeong.

17
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:50,067
Can I start my love story

18
00:01:50,526 --> 00:01:53,029
with this man, whom I've just met downtown

19
00:01:53,863 --> 00:01:57,742
exactly at 7 o'clock?

20
00:01:57,825 --> 00:01:59,619
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE
EPISODE 1

21
00:02:01,579 --> 00:02:05,082
A MONTH AGO

22
00:02:13,841 --> 00:02:15,259
What's the point of the alarm

23
00:02:16,177 --> 00:02:18,804
if you're not even going to wake up?

24
00:02:19,221 --> 00:02:22,016
- Wake up already!
- Come on!

25
00:02:22,141 --> 00:02:24,393
Your clothes are all over the floor.

26
00:02:25,603 --> 00:02:28,230
Stop putting your garbage on the bedframe!

27
00:02:28,314 --> 00:02:30,858
- Clean up after yourself, will you?
- Mom!

28
00:02:30,941 --> 00:02:33,778
I'm trying to sleep here.
Why are you being so loud?

29
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:42,161
I see. I understand.

30
00:02:42,745 --> 00:02:44,997
But I wouldn't recommend
canceling your insurance.

31
00:02:45,206 --> 00:02:49,210
It may be hard to sign up again
because of your medical history.

32
00:02:50,503 --> 00:02:53,881
People your age start needing surgery

33
00:02:53,964 --> 00:02:56,133
for various illnesses.

34
00:02:56,759 --> 00:02:58,094
I understand.

35
00:02:58,177 --> 00:02:59,178
CHORE TABLE

36
00:02:59,261 --> 00:03:01,180
I understand that the economy is bad.

37
00:03:01,263 --> 00:03:03,557
I get a lot of calls
about contract cancellations.

38
00:03:03,641 --> 00:03:05,434
Working hard, I see, even on the weekend.

39
00:03:05,518 --> 00:03:07,520
But it costs as much as a weekend brunch.

40
00:03:07,603 --> 00:03:09,188
It's wiser to invest in your health

41
00:03:09,271 --> 00:03:11,524
and reduce unnecessary spending.
Aren't I right?

42
00:03:12,108 --> 00:03:14,443
- She's good.
- How about wedding money?

43
00:03:14,527 --> 00:03:16,278
Very in line with the current time.

44
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:17,363
The inflation, too.

45
00:03:17,446 --> 00:03:20,282
I'm sure you spend a lot on weddings
at your age.

46
00:03:21,158 --> 00:03:24,161
Don't attend so many weddings
if you aren't getting married.

47
00:03:25,162 --> 00:03:28,416
I stopped going to weddings a while ago

48
00:03:28,499 --> 00:03:30,376
since I know my daughter won't have one.

49
00:03:31,168 --> 00:03:33,713
That's too much confidence.

50
00:03:33,796 --> 00:03:35,631
That's insurance I'd never buy.

51
00:03:36,424 --> 00:03:37,466
Huh?

52
00:03:38,217 --> 00:03:39,927
You're lying, right?

53
00:03:40,010 --> 00:03:43,347
You're still sending wedding money,
even if you don't attend them, right?

54
00:03:43,431 --> 00:03:44,724
- No.
- "No"?

55
00:03:44,807 --> 00:03:47,059
I take pride in my work
as an insurance broker.

56
00:03:47,143 --> 00:03:49,562
I don't lie to my customers
for the sake of more sales.

57
00:03:50,187 --> 00:03:53,482
Why is this a big deal?
Does this really make you that sad?

58
00:03:53,566 --> 00:03:55,025
Of course, it does!

59
00:03:55,109 --> 00:03:57,820
Isn't it a mother's joy to raise her kid

60
00:03:57,903 --> 00:03:59,321
and wait to see her thrive?

61
00:03:59,405 --> 00:04:01,824
Waiting around won't change anything.

62
00:04:02,700 --> 00:04:05,703
That's a waste.
You haven't dated in so long

63
00:04:05,786 --> 00:04:08,205
that I thought you were
against dating and marriage.

64
00:04:08,289 --> 00:04:11,459
Not at all. I'm against neither.

65
00:04:11,792 --> 00:04:13,085
I just...

66
00:04:13,169 --> 00:04:16,213
Oh, so, you just can't find a man?

67
00:04:17,089 --> 00:04:18,257
Four years.

68
00:04:19,258 --> 00:04:22,970
Remember your ex, who broke up with you
while I was getting my trainer license?

69
00:04:23,929 --> 00:04:26,682
Don't you remember crying
and coming to the gym every day?

70
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:30,603
You even made your dumbbell slippery
from all that crying.

71
00:04:33,647 --> 00:04:35,024
Hasn't it only been four months?

72
00:04:35,107 --> 00:04:37,193
How is that already four years ago?

73
00:04:37,318 --> 00:04:40,571
As people get old and frail

74
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:43,157
they process life more slowly

75
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:45,659
making time feel like it flies.

76
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:50,039
So, let's do your next set of squats.

77
00:04:51,457 --> 00:04:53,250
Can you not call it "aging"?

78
00:04:53,334 --> 00:04:56,712
Can you call it "becoming mature
and growing wiser"?

79
00:04:56,796 --> 00:04:57,922
No.

80
00:04:58,714 --> 00:04:59,757
Here.

81
00:05:01,008 --> 00:05:02,676
Go down, and hold for four seconds.

82
00:05:03,135 --> 00:05:04,220
One.

83
00:05:05,304 --> 00:05:06,847
You've come a long way.

84
00:05:06,931 --> 00:05:09,391
You couldn't even hold 1kg,
but you can carry 4kg now.

85
00:05:10,559 --> 00:05:11,685
Two.

86
00:05:11,852 --> 00:05:13,813
You're respected
by your younger colleagues

87
00:05:13,896 --> 00:05:16,440
while becoming a threat to your seniors.
Aren't I right?

88
00:05:17,191 --> 00:05:18,400
Wait, I'm getting a call.

89
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:22,238
Huh?

90
00:05:23,864 --> 00:05:25,241
- Hey, Na-ri.
- Ui-yeong!

91
00:05:25,324 --> 00:05:27,660
What have you done?
Come to the hotel right now!

92
00:05:31,330 --> 00:05:34,333
The restaurant's sous chef called,
and they're seriously short on cod.

93
00:05:34,458 --> 00:05:36,669
For the British Embassy reception tonight.

94
00:05:36,877 --> 00:05:38,629
All the attendees for the event chose

95
00:05:38,712 --> 00:05:40,631
their dietary preferences... Watch out!

96
00:05:40,965 --> 00:05:43,759
We planned the menu accordingly

97
00:05:43,843 --> 00:05:45,386
and purchased the right quantities.

98
00:05:45,469 --> 00:05:48,055
- But not predicted the Embassy's request.
- What?

99
00:05:48,138 --> 00:05:51,100
The dishes weren't British enough,
so they asked to add fish and chips.

100
00:05:51,183 --> 00:05:52,268
What?

101
00:05:52,768 --> 00:05:53,978
We don't have time.

102
00:05:54,061 --> 00:05:56,188
Buy 80 whole cod
and return to the hotel by 2 p.m.

103
00:05:56,272 --> 00:05:57,982
By 2 p.m.? That many cod?

104
00:05:58,065 --> 00:06:00,234
Where and how can I possibly...

105
00:06:00,317 --> 00:06:02,528
Where? Why are you asking me that?

106
00:06:04,071 --> 00:06:05,823
Mr. Eun!

107
00:06:06,657 --> 00:06:09,118
Sorry, my crew can be
so short-sighted at times.

108
00:06:10,035 --> 00:06:13,122
But don't worry.
We'll get everything on time.

109
00:06:13,205 --> 00:06:16,125
- Thanks for your hard work.
- It's nothing.

110
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:18,168
Place that over there.

111
00:06:18,252 --> 00:06:19,295
Got it.

112
00:06:20,337 --> 00:06:22,047
- Hello.
- Keep up the good work.

113
00:06:22,131 --> 00:06:23,424
Thank you, sir.

114
00:06:23,924 --> 00:06:25,426
Please keep up the good work.

115
00:06:34,727 --> 00:06:37,688
How can they add more to the menu
on the day of the event?

116
00:06:37,771 --> 00:06:41,233
The assistant begged for it,
promising to book with us next time.

117
00:06:42,109 --> 00:06:43,861
The hotel can't say no to that.

118
00:06:44,486 --> 00:06:46,572
Do you think we can get 80 whole cod here?

119
00:06:46,655 --> 00:06:49,617
- We have to, no matter what.
- That's insane.

120
00:06:52,286 --> 00:06:53,329
CLAMS, SCALLOPS, MUSSELS

121
00:06:55,164 --> 00:06:58,542
I thought you dressed
very casually for work

122
00:06:58,626 --> 00:07:01,629
but I can now see
that you dress up to the tens. So cute!

123
00:07:01,712 --> 00:07:04,006
I had to come
in the middle of my workout today, okay?

124
00:07:04,423 --> 00:07:06,342
How many cod do we have so far?

125
00:07:06,425 --> 00:07:08,469
We got ten from the market

126
00:07:08,552 --> 00:07:11,847
and ordered 20 more for delivery.
We still need 50 more.

127
00:07:11,931 --> 00:07:13,432
- Hey!
- Uncle.

128
00:07:13,515 --> 00:07:16,977
I hear you're buying
every cod from the market.

129
00:07:17,144 --> 00:07:19,229
Sorry, this is all we have.

130
00:07:19,313 --> 00:07:20,773
- Really?
- We'll take them all.

131
00:07:20,856 --> 00:07:24,109
Why are there no cod today?
This is the last shop we're checking.

132
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:25,861
Is there a way to get more?

133
00:07:25,945 --> 00:07:28,489
People bought them all already.
I'll pack these for you.

134
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:32,368
- Uncle.
- Yeah?

135
00:07:32,451 --> 00:07:34,828
You know the cod
for the SEASON PLAZA HOTEL?

136
00:07:34,912 --> 00:07:35,913
What? Gosh.

137
00:07:36,413 --> 00:07:38,374
Come on. There are rules.

138
00:07:38,457 --> 00:07:40,584
I can't give you other people's orders.

139
00:07:40,960 --> 00:07:42,002
No.

140
00:07:42,670 --> 00:07:44,296
- Hyun-min.
- Yeah?

141
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:46,423
Take those and go back to the hotel first.

142
00:07:46,507 --> 00:07:47,591
What about you?

143
00:07:47,675 --> 00:07:49,218
I know where the cod are going now.

144
00:07:49,301 --> 00:07:51,136
I have to go, then. To get the fish.

145
00:08:06,318 --> 00:08:08,570
Hello, are you here to check in?

146
00:08:08,654 --> 00:08:11,782
No, I'm not. I just need some help.

147
00:08:12,950 --> 00:08:14,368
What do you need help with?

148
00:08:14,451 --> 00:08:15,744
I need to know a number.

149
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:17,955
This is

150
00:08:18,998 --> 00:08:20,332
my business card.

151
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:22,960
LEE UI-YEONG, FROM PURCHASING TEAM
THE HILLS SEOUL

152
00:08:23,043 --> 00:08:26,005
I really need the number of the Manager
of the Purchasing Team here.

153
00:08:32,970 --> 00:08:35,848
They look great, but we need more.

154
00:08:35,931 --> 00:08:38,851
Chef, with all due respect

155
00:08:38,934 --> 00:08:40,936
can't you make the portions
slightly smaller?

156
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:44,023
Make the fish look big
by using a lot of fry batter...

157
00:08:44,106 --> 00:08:45,607
That's nonsense.

158
00:08:46,275 --> 00:08:49,653
Chef, how about we make up for it
with some salad or garnish?

159
00:08:49,737 --> 00:08:51,822
- That's the same.
- Exactly.

160
00:08:58,579 --> 00:08:59,830
"SEASON PLAZA"?

161
00:09:00,706 --> 00:09:01,832
Thank you!

162
00:09:04,209 --> 00:09:05,836
Ui-yeong!

163
00:09:06,336 --> 00:09:08,338
Why are you getting out of this truck?

164
00:09:12,092 --> 00:09:14,178
30 MINUTES AGO

165
00:09:22,019 --> 00:09:23,020
MANAGER CHO ARAM OF PURCHASING TEAM

166
00:09:23,604 --> 00:09:26,648
I've always wanted to meet you.
You know me, right?

167
00:09:26,899 --> 00:09:29,068
I'm Ui-yeong from the Purchasing Team
at The Hills.

168
00:09:29,151 --> 00:09:31,528
Yeah, I know. Why are you here?

169
00:09:31,612 --> 00:09:33,739
You know the cod shipment you got today?

170
00:09:33,989 --> 00:09:35,491
Give it all to me.

171
00:09:36,492 --> 00:09:38,118
And why should I do that?

172
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:39,244
Why else?

173
00:09:41,580 --> 00:09:42,748
Because it's an emergency.

174
00:09:42,873 --> 00:09:45,834
Why else would I ask
a competitor for help?

175
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:47,753
Ms. Lee

176
00:09:47,836 --> 00:09:50,214
you're a lot more brazen than I expected.

177
00:09:50,589 --> 00:09:53,092
- Good for you.
- But not for free.

178
00:09:53,342 --> 00:09:54,968
You've been looking for trout, right?

179
00:09:55,761 --> 00:09:56,804
Trout?

180
00:10:09,399 --> 00:10:11,401
HACCP-approved trout grown

181
00:10:11,485 --> 00:10:14,488
on a farm run for two generations
in the clearest valley water.

182
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,826
Gosh, it's so fatty and flavorful.

183
00:10:18,909 --> 00:10:21,620
I'm sure you know it well,
since you've had it yourself.

184
00:10:21,995 --> 00:10:23,080
Me?

185
00:10:23,539 --> 00:10:25,249
I'll connect you to a trout farm.

186
00:10:33,966 --> 00:10:34,967
You sure?

187
00:10:41,056 --> 00:10:42,474
Prep these now.

188
00:10:42,558 --> 00:10:43,642
- Yes, Chef.
- Yes, Chef.

189
00:10:45,477 --> 00:10:47,354
Are you crazy, Ui-yeong?

190
00:10:47,646 --> 00:10:50,315
How did you even think
of buying from our competitor?

191
00:10:50,941 --> 00:10:52,860
I'm just glad we got them.

192
00:10:53,277 --> 00:10:56,238
I thought I might need to look
for a spot on the earliest fishing boat.

193
00:10:58,115 --> 00:11:01,368
You know, she means that, too.

194
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:05,539
You may not really know it
since you're new here

195
00:11:05,622 --> 00:11:09,668
but Ui-yeong will come to the rescue
all the time.

196
00:11:09,751 --> 00:11:11,086
- Gosh.
- Looking forward to it.

197
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:13,297
- Looking forward to working with you.
- Okay.

198
00:11:14,882 --> 00:11:18,260
- You're the best!
- What a relief.

199
00:11:22,347 --> 00:11:24,099
Why do my fingers still smell fishy?

200
00:11:24,183 --> 00:11:25,726
- Right?
- Yeah.

201
00:11:25,809 --> 00:11:27,311
I have a date tonight.

202
00:11:27,394 --> 00:11:28,520
Look at me.

203
00:11:29,062 --> 00:11:31,148
"You want to shower first?" Do I smell?

204
00:11:31,481 --> 00:11:33,609
It's like I'm touching a cod.
Don't touch me.

205
00:11:33,692 --> 00:11:34,943
- Really?
- Yeah.

206
00:11:35,027 --> 00:11:36,361
What should I do?

207
00:11:36,737 --> 00:11:37,863
They stink.

208
00:11:38,780 --> 00:11:40,866
We need to talk.

209
00:11:46,246 --> 00:11:47,956
THE HILLS SEOUL
EMPLOYEE OF THE MONTH

210
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:51,168
Respect the rules. How embarrassing.

211
00:11:51,251 --> 00:11:54,004
You really showed our competitors
that we were bad at our job?

212
00:11:54,087 --> 00:11:57,507
You think you're amazing at your job,
don't you? No.

213
00:11:57,591 --> 00:11:59,968
Had you understood our client perfectly

214
00:12:00,052 --> 00:12:02,304
we wouldn't have needed extra staff today.

215
00:12:02,387 --> 00:12:04,932
We're the Purchasing Team, not psychics.

216
00:12:05,098 --> 00:12:07,100
How were we supposed to see this coming?

217
00:12:07,893 --> 00:12:10,520
You could've, if you stayed focused.

218
00:12:10,604 --> 00:12:12,397
You don't have a family or a boyfriend.

219
00:12:12,481 --> 00:12:14,107
Work is the only thing on your plate.

220
00:12:14,191 --> 00:12:16,610
We have a lot more on our plates, alright?

221
00:12:16,693 --> 00:12:19,404
Forget it.
There's no point in talking to you.

222
00:12:19,488 --> 00:12:23,325
Submit a report on what happened
and the receipt by Monday.

223
00:12:35,003 --> 00:12:36,004
REPORT
I'M SORRY FOR BEING GOOD AT MY JOB!

224
00:12:38,465 --> 00:12:42,302
I didn't expect her to thank us
for solving the problem.

225
00:12:42,594 --> 00:12:46,974
But how can she bring
our personal lives into this?

226
00:12:47,516 --> 00:12:49,101
Aren't you annoyed?

227
00:12:49,184 --> 00:12:51,603
Why not? But what can we do?
We have to write that report.

228
00:12:52,187 --> 00:12:54,982
Should I just get a boyfriend?

229
00:12:55,065 --> 00:12:56,650
Do you want me to set you up?

230
00:12:56,900 --> 00:13:00,570
Let's show her
that we have our steamy love lives, too.

231
00:13:00,654 --> 00:13:03,282
I'm not going on a blind date
just to prove a point.

232
00:13:03,365 --> 00:13:05,826
So, no blind date? Something less serious?

233
00:13:05,909 --> 00:13:08,495
I have more ideas, then!

234
00:13:09,162 --> 00:13:10,247
Let's see.

235
00:13:11,331 --> 00:13:12,374
Look at this.

236
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:13,875
What's this?

237
00:13:19,798 --> 00:13:21,800
There's no photo of his face.

238
00:13:21,883 --> 00:13:22,926
Really?

239
00:13:23,593 --> 00:13:24,636
"Really?"

240
00:13:25,137 --> 00:13:26,888
You date guys without seeing their faces?

241
00:13:27,097 --> 00:13:29,141
What if you meet a creep?

242
00:13:29,224 --> 00:13:30,559
But his body is hot.

243
00:13:30,642 --> 00:13:32,436
And his head is attached to the body.

244
00:13:34,938 --> 00:13:36,440
What is this?

245
00:13:36,523 --> 00:13:38,692
The eggplant and peach emojis?

246
00:13:39,776 --> 00:13:42,863
Eggplant and peach!

247
00:13:44,156 --> 00:13:45,866
Hey!

248
00:13:46,950 --> 00:13:48,410
Stop it, seriously.

249
00:13:49,202 --> 00:13:50,704
Cut it out.

250
00:13:51,288 --> 00:13:55,625
You don't want me to set you up,
but you don't want to use the app?

251
00:13:56,460 --> 00:13:58,545
- Do you have a guy already?
- You think?

252
00:13:58,628 --> 00:14:00,672
I'm here, working on the weekend.

253
00:14:02,507 --> 00:14:03,508
Right.

254
00:14:09,639 --> 00:14:11,016
CHATS

255
00:14:11,099 --> 00:14:12,976
Did you sort out the emergency?

256
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:17,856
I'm still working on it.

257
00:14:19,316 --> 00:14:22,235
Perfect. I'm heading to the office
to get some files.

258
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:23,945
You want to grab dinner with me?

259
00:14:24,905 --> 00:14:26,573
I do have someone.

260
00:14:27,949 --> 00:14:29,868
Hyun-min, you said you had a dinner date.

261
00:14:29,951 --> 00:14:31,578
I'll finish it up. You can go first.

262
00:14:31,661 --> 00:14:33,288
- What? Really?
- Yeah.

263
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:37,167
- Leave. Or I'll leave.
- Right on!

264
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:40,087
Thanks so much.

265
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:42,089
Have this.

266
00:14:42,506 --> 00:14:44,758
- Bye.
- Bye! See you.

267
00:14:44,841 --> 00:14:45,884
See you.

268
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:49,638
This is why I'm not interested
in dating apps or a blind date.

269
00:14:51,848 --> 00:14:55,268
Here's for working so hard
over the weekend. Eat up.

270
00:14:56,269 --> 00:14:58,730
- Thanks.
- He's the reason.

271
00:14:58,814 --> 00:15:00,941
You don't need to address me
as "Ms. Lee" at work.

272
00:15:01,024 --> 00:15:03,652
You work in the Legal Department.
I'm not your manager.

273
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:07,155
I'm working on it, but I'm so used to it.

274
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,409
Do-hyun was in one class after mine
in college.

275
00:15:10,951 --> 00:15:13,745
I heard he'd become a lawyer
after graduation

276
00:15:13,829 --> 00:15:16,706
and he recently started working

277
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:18,917
as the Legal Advisor at my hotel.

278
00:15:19,793 --> 00:15:21,920
- Can you pass me a tissue?
- Yeah.

279
00:15:25,590 --> 00:15:26,633
What's wrong?

280
00:15:26,883 --> 00:15:30,303
I had to buy fish at the market earlier.

281
00:15:30,554 --> 00:15:32,931
I usually wear gloves,
but I forgot them today.

282
00:15:34,307 --> 00:15:35,976
- Hey...
- It's fine.

283
00:15:36,059 --> 00:15:37,394
It smells like hand lotion.

284
00:15:37,477 --> 00:15:38,812
What product is it? It's nice.

285
00:15:41,565 --> 00:15:43,692
I hadn't seen him in forever since college

286
00:15:43,775 --> 00:15:47,112
but he's suddenly entered my life
and is making my heart skip a beat.

287
00:15:56,913 --> 00:15:59,124
You look good today.

288
00:15:59,749 --> 00:16:01,042
What's the occasion?

289
00:16:03,670 --> 00:16:05,046
A colleague's wedding.

290
00:16:05,547 --> 00:16:08,592
I told my friends from college
that I now work at your hotel

291
00:16:08,675 --> 00:16:11,511
and everyone teased me,
saying I did it on purpose.

292
00:16:12,471 --> 00:16:13,638
Really?

293
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:17,184
I was really surprised to see you
at the hotel.

294
00:16:17,267 --> 00:16:18,602
- Were you?
- Yeah.

295
00:16:18,685 --> 00:16:20,562
You look so different now.

296
00:16:20,645 --> 00:16:22,481
I even thought you were someone else.

297
00:16:23,273 --> 00:16:26,109
Have I changed that much?

298
00:16:26,276 --> 00:16:27,319
Yeah.

299
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:31,156
The guys asked if you were still pretty,
so I told them you were the same.

300
00:16:33,575 --> 00:16:36,661
You don't need to go along with that.

301
00:16:36,953 --> 00:16:39,664
I wasn't lying. You're pretty.

302
00:16:46,004 --> 00:16:47,297
Keep eating.

303
00:16:54,679 --> 00:16:55,931
Have more.

304
00:16:58,058 --> 00:16:59,184
Thank you.

305
00:17:03,522 --> 00:17:05,941
Do you still live on the hill?

306
00:17:06,274 --> 00:17:08,860
Yeah, you remember that?

307
00:17:14,783 --> 00:17:16,743
Get in. I'll drive you home.

308
00:17:17,911 --> 00:17:20,080
He said the same thing back then.

309
00:17:22,624 --> 00:17:24,251
- What should we eat?
- Tteokbokki.

310
00:17:24,334 --> 00:17:26,169
- I found a new restaurant.
- Ui-yeong!

311
00:17:29,214 --> 00:17:31,758
- I'll call you later.
- But back then

312
00:17:31,841 --> 00:17:35,512
Do-hyun drove a red bicycle, not a car.

313
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,141
Let's go. I'll take you home.

314
00:17:54,030 --> 00:17:55,115
Hey.

315
00:17:56,074 --> 00:17:59,119
I live at the top of this hill.
I can go alone from here.

316
00:18:00,328 --> 00:18:01,329
Oh.

317
00:18:02,747 --> 00:18:04,457
Let's go. I'll walk you.

318
00:18:22,976 --> 00:18:25,145
Thank you. Get home safe.

319
00:18:25,228 --> 00:18:26,646
Wait!

320
00:18:26,771 --> 00:18:28,356
I have something to say.

321
00:18:50,170 --> 00:18:52,839
- What are you doing?
- I like you!

322
00:18:52,922 --> 00:18:55,091
Since the first day I met you
in the club room.

323
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:58,011
You were the only one I could see.
Everything else was a blur.

324
00:18:58,094 --> 00:19:00,889
Do-hyun was a hopeless romantic.

325
00:19:01,056 --> 00:19:03,308
- Come on. Get up.
- You're beautiful

326
00:19:03,391 --> 00:19:06,186
so you don't need to work so hard,
but you do.

327
00:19:06,978 --> 00:19:08,605
You're different from girls my age.

328
00:19:08,772 --> 00:19:10,982
But as with most first loves

329
00:19:11,066 --> 00:19:13,610
it was too rushed and unrequited.

330
00:19:14,569 --> 00:19:17,739
Be my girlfriend!
I promise to make you happy!

331
00:19:22,243 --> 00:19:23,870
And back then...

332
00:19:24,245 --> 00:19:26,414
Sorry, I can't.

333
00:19:31,086 --> 00:19:33,755
- Enjoy.
- Life was already hard enough.

334
00:19:34,297 --> 00:19:36,341
I had no interest in dating.

335
00:19:37,175 --> 00:19:39,010
Whatever love was

336
00:19:39,803 --> 00:19:42,639
I knew I wasn't ready for it.

337
00:19:45,850 --> 00:19:47,977
You say I work hard

338
00:19:48,436 --> 00:19:51,815
but no, I work like my life depends on it.

339
00:19:52,357 --> 00:19:54,192
There's no space for dating in my life.

340
00:19:56,403 --> 00:19:57,487
I can...

341
00:19:58,655 --> 00:19:59,656
No.

342
00:20:01,199 --> 00:20:02,283
Sorry.

343
00:20:03,284 --> 00:20:05,370
Let's just pretend this never happened.

344
00:20:37,444 --> 00:20:38,987
But the current Do-hyun is

345
00:20:39,279 --> 00:20:41,698
a whole different person from then.

346
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:52,375
Thanks so much for today. Drive safe.

347
00:20:53,585 --> 00:20:55,253
- Ui-yeong.
- Yeah?

348
00:20:55,670 --> 00:20:58,298
Are you seeing anyone?

349
00:20:58,381 --> 00:20:59,966
The guys wanted to know.

350
00:21:01,509 --> 00:21:02,761
No.

351
00:21:03,178 --> 00:21:06,681
Why not?
Are you still not interested in dating?

352
00:21:08,141 --> 00:21:11,686
Well, I'm interested,
but there's nobody to date.

353
00:21:11,770 --> 00:21:13,938
I'm only ever home or at work.

354
00:21:14,022 --> 00:21:15,857
I have no chance to meet anyone.

355
00:21:16,357 --> 00:21:17,525
It doesn't have to be

356
00:21:18,568 --> 00:21:20,779
someone new, does it?

357
00:21:21,237 --> 00:21:24,449
- What?
- I'm sure there's a good man somewhere.

358
00:21:27,619 --> 00:21:30,789
Is he talking about himself?

359
00:21:35,877 --> 00:21:38,046
I'm home!

360
00:21:38,630 --> 00:21:39,756
Hey, Mom.

361
00:21:44,010 --> 00:21:45,470
She was so cranky in the morning.

362
00:21:46,805 --> 00:21:48,681
Why is she so happy now?

363
00:22:15,208 --> 00:22:16,793
I was always curious.

364
00:22:17,210 --> 00:22:19,504
The hotel isn't so big,
and there's so much work.

365
00:22:19,796 --> 00:22:22,340
I always wondered
how everyone started dating coworkers.

366
00:22:25,718 --> 00:22:27,303
I bet nobody knows

367
00:22:27,637 --> 00:22:30,098
that we work underground with no sunlight.

368
00:22:31,057 --> 00:22:33,059
Get as much sunlight as possible now.

369
00:22:35,645 --> 00:22:37,438
It's so nice.

370
00:22:48,324 --> 00:22:50,910
Coffee is on us today.

371
00:22:51,995 --> 00:22:53,913
- Thank you!
- Thanks.

372
00:22:53,997 --> 00:22:55,081
Thank you.

373
00:22:55,164 --> 00:22:56,291
Nice.

374
00:22:58,376 --> 00:23:00,086
I also like chocolate, you know?

375
00:23:00,169 --> 00:23:01,546
Next time.

376
00:23:01,963 --> 00:23:03,047
Sure.

377
00:23:03,339 --> 00:23:04,591
Thank you.

378
00:23:04,924 --> 00:23:06,843
Thank you!

379
00:23:06,926 --> 00:23:08,761
For eight hours a day

380
00:23:09,137 --> 00:23:10,930
we shared
the same meeting room, rooftop

381
00:23:12,974 --> 00:23:15,894
and the same vending machine

382
00:23:16,019 --> 00:23:19,022
and we grew much closer
than I'd ever expected.

383
00:23:26,446 --> 00:23:29,365
- How many are there?
- My gosh, so many.

384
00:23:56,476 --> 00:23:58,061
Wasn't that so funny?

385
00:23:59,270 --> 00:24:00,688
- Here.
- What?

386
00:24:01,439 --> 00:24:03,316
Oh, gosh, I got something on my shirt.

387
00:24:03,816 --> 00:24:05,318
- Hello, sir.
- Hey.

388
00:24:05,401 --> 00:24:06,861
Where are you going?

389
00:24:07,570 --> 00:24:09,614
- Just to my office.
- I see.

390
00:24:09,697 --> 00:24:11,324
And you? Getting coffee?

391
00:24:11,574 --> 00:24:14,118
Yes, sir. I'm just so tired.

392
00:24:14,243 --> 00:24:16,454
- Sure, then.
- Have a good one.

393
00:24:16,537 --> 00:24:17,830
Oh, right.

394
00:24:20,249 --> 00:24:21,417
Do you...

395
00:24:24,504 --> 00:24:26,089
maybe want to go on a blind date?

396
00:24:26,839 --> 00:24:29,133
- What?
- You're single.

397
00:24:30,718 --> 00:24:33,763
He volunteers at the dog shelter with me.

398
00:24:33,846 --> 00:24:36,766
He's such a serious, kind guy.

399
00:24:36,849 --> 00:24:38,017
- He's...
- I'm fine!

400
00:24:38,101 --> 00:24:39,894
I'm not interested in a blind date.

401
00:24:39,978 --> 00:24:42,730
Gosh, not at all. I'm not into that.

402
00:24:43,147 --> 00:24:45,650
You don't even need to think about it?

403
00:24:47,318 --> 00:24:48,403
Sure, then.

404
00:24:49,278 --> 00:24:50,613
- Okay.
- Bye.

405
00:24:50,697 --> 00:24:52,073
- Have a good day.
- Okay.

406
00:25:01,332 --> 00:25:04,377
Maybe 80% of my love for my job isn't
about the job.

407
00:25:11,801 --> 00:25:13,344
I can't wait to go to work.

408
00:25:15,805 --> 00:25:17,724
You've finally lost it.

409
00:25:17,849 --> 00:25:21,811
Maybe it's tachycardia, not flutters.
You did your health checkup, right?

410
00:25:21,894 --> 00:25:24,480
Hey, you think I can't tell the difference
between the two?

411
00:25:24,564 --> 00:25:26,107
No, I doubt it.

412
00:25:26,190 --> 00:25:27,483
Don't be a jerk.

413
00:25:28,735 --> 00:25:32,113
You're once again the only one
drinking and eating chicken feet, right?

414
00:25:32,196 --> 00:25:33,948
- Of course.
- Yes.

415
00:25:34,157 --> 00:25:37,076
Could you microwave these for me?

416
00:25:37,160 --> 00:25:38,870
Two minutes, with the packaging off.

417
00:25:39,495 --> 00:25:41,205
I don't want to eat microplastics.

418
00:25:44,042 --> 00:25:46,127
- Only because you're a regular.
- Thank you.

419
00:25:46,919 --> 00:25:50,465
How are you two dating
when you eat so differently?

420
00:25:50,548 --> 00:25:53,009
- We're just friends!
- And I can't even handle that!

421
00:25:54,844 --> 00:25:56,262
Alright, I get it.

422
00:25:56,637 --> 00:25:58,806
No need to get so worked up.

423
00:25:58,890 --> 00:26:00,475
My gosh. You're kidding.

424
00:26:00,558 --> 00:26:01,601
Don't say that again!

425
00:26:01,684 --> 00:26:03,311
I was having a good day.

426
00:26:03,394 --> 00:26:04,771
Me too, alright?

427
00:26:04,854 --> 00:26:06,064
Anything else?

428
00:26:06,147 --> 00:26:07,857
BELOVED TREASURE
WE'RE ALL A TREASURE TO SOMEONE

429
00:26:08,191 --> 00:26:10,818
So, did Do-hyun ask you out?

430
00:26:11,819 --> 00:26:16,199
As I always say, men are simple.
We don't send mixed messages.

431
00:26:16,449 --> 00:26:17,617
I'm not confused at all.

432
00:26:18,117 --> 00:26:19,827
I know I haven't told you this

433
00:26:20,745 --> 00:26:22,121
but I'm

434
00:26:23,331 --> 00:26:24,540
his first love.

435
00:26:24,916 --> 00:26:25,958
What?

436
00:26:27,502 --> 00:26:28,961
First love? That's huge.

437
00:26:30,838 --> 00:26:33,883
He asked me out once,
and I turned him down.

438
00:26:33,966 --> 00:26:36,385
As you know,
my interest in dating in college was

439
00:26:36,469 --> 00:26:38,930
less than dirt under a chicken's claw.

440
00:26:39,013 --> 00:26:42,266
"Dirt under a chicken's claw"? Seriously?

441
00:26:42,850 --> 00:26:46,395
So, now that you have time to date,
you want to date him?

442
00:26:46,687 --> 00:26:47,730
Yeah.

443
00:26:48,981 --> 00:26:50,191
But do you think

444
00:26:50,817 --> 00:26:53,444
he may be hesitant about asking me out

445
00:26:53,528 --> 00:26:55,905
because I rejected him once?

446
00:26:58,699 --> 00:27:00,576
Yeah, that'd definitely affect him.

447
00:27:01,536 --> 00:27:03,412
Show him you're interested now.

448
00:27:03,538 --> 00:27:05,248
Make him ask you out again.

449
00:27:05,665 --> 00:27:06,833
How?

450
00:27:06,916 --> 00:27:08,000
Well...

451
00:27:08,793 --> 00:27:10,920
Spend some alone time with him.

452
00:27:11,003 --> 00:27:12,046
How?

453
00:27:13,214 --> 00:27:14,674
Grab a drink with him.

454
00:27:15,675 --> 00:27:17,844
Perfect. What should we drink?

455
00:27:18,219 --> 00:27:19,345
A light beer?

456
00:27:19,428 --> 00:27:20,972
Or soju for some drunken truth?

457
00:27:22,515 --> 00:27:25,226
Or champagne for romance?

458
00:27:31,774 --> 00:27:33,401
Ui-yeong

459
00:27:33,484 --> 00:27:35,695
do we have to visit the producer
on site visits?

460
00:27:35,778 --> 00:27:37,905
Oh, you know

461
00:27:37,989 --> 00:27:40,491
how we first sign a purchase contract
with a producer

462
00:27:40,575 --> 00:27:44,287
and mostly purchase the products online
after that?

463
00:27:44,370 --> 00:27:46,747
Site visits are to check
if the producers are still good.

464
00:27:46,873 --> 00:27:49,292
We check for any changes
since the contract signing

465
00:27:49,375 --> 00:27:51,586
and if we can continue to buy from them.

466
00:27:51,669 --> 00:27:55,131
They're all great.
They welcome us when we visit.

467
00:27:55,214 --> 00:27:56,507
I see.

468
00:27:56,883 --> 00:27:59,677
So, who wants to go to Boseong?

469
00:28:01,304 --> 00:28:04,348
Nobody wants to step up for the team?

470
00:28:04,891 --> 00:28:07,310
Hyun-min and I went

471
00:28:07,602 --> 00:28:09,937
last year.

472
00:28:10,021 --> 00:28:12,315
- Really? This time...
- Did you?

473
00:28:12,398 --> 00:28:14,192
I thought I went.

474
00:28:14,525 --> 00:28:17,445
It's too bad.
You'll have to go again this year.

475
00:28:17,528 --> 00:28:19,614
My father-in-law's birthday is
this weekend.

476
00:28:19,697 --> 00:28:21,324
- Really? Then...
- Oh!

477
00:28:22,533 --> 00:28:25,036
Wasn't it his birthday last month?

478
00:28:25,703 --> 00:28:29,373
How does he have two birthdays?

479
00:28:29,582 --> 00:28:31,626
- That's odd.
- Is that so?

480
00:28:31,918 --> 00:28:34,086
No, that wasn't my father-in-law.

481
00:28:34,170 --> 00:28:36,297
It was my brother-in-law.

482
00:28:36,714 --> 00:28:38,382
You don't get it because you're single.

483
00:28:38,466 --> 00:28:40,009
Family gatherings are important.

484
00:28:40,092 --> 00:28:42,220
Since I have to do my groceries

485
00:28:42,303 --> 00:28:45,514
it just makes sense
that I visit the Mapo site.

486
00:28:45,598 --> 00:28:49,310
It makes more sense for all of us
to visit Mapo.

487
00:28:49,393 --> 00:28:51,437
Alright, stop it.

488
00:28:51,687 --> 00:28:53,189
She has a family to care for.

489
00:28:53,272 --> 00:28:55,024
You two can go. It's a trip.

490
00:28:55,274 --> 00:28:57,151
- Mr. Oh!
- What?

491
00:29:00,404 --> 00:29:01,447
Got a problem?

492
00:29:02,323 --> 00:29:03,491
SITE VISIT SCHEDULE

493
00:29:03,574 --> 00:29:05,117
MAPO: JUNG NA-RI, YEOJU: OH MYEONG-UN,
BOSEONG: UI-YEONG, HYUN-MIN

494
00:29:07,119 --> 00:29:08,871
Just one more year this year.

495
00:29:08,955 --> 00:29:11,374
I'll do whatever it takes
to get out of this next year.

496
00:29:12,959 --> 00:29:14,335
What about you, Sae-byeok?

497
00:29:14,627 --> 00:29:17,672
I'll join you two and go to Boseong.

498
00:29:17,755 --> 00:29:19,215
I did some research

499
00:29:19,298 --> 00:29:21,133
and a lot of movies were shot
in the fields.

500
00:29:21,217 --> 00:29:22,927
It's also known to be a great date spot.

501
00:29:23,302 --> 00:29:24,679
Really?

502
00:29:25,221 --> 00:29:29,183
Who cares about how cute Boseong is?
We're not going there for fun.

503
00:29:29,267 --> 00:29:31,477
That's true. Sorry.

504
00:29:31,560 --> 00:29:34,105
No need to be sorry. It makes work fun.

505
00:29:34,188 --> 00:29:37,149
We can have a fun trip there
once we're done with the site visit.

506
00:29:37,233 --> 00:29:38,317
That sounds great!

507
00:29:41,195 --> 00:29:42,405
Alright, then.

508
00:29:42,488 --> 00:29:43,906
BOSEONG: UI-YEONG, HYUN-MIN, SAE-BYEOK

509
00:29:43,990 --> 00:29:45,283
I'll take this.

510
00:29:46,575 --> 00:29:47,743
Alright!

511
00:29:49,870 --> 00:29:52,707
Ui-yeong, meet me in the break room
after the meeting.

512
00:29:55,293 --> 00:29:57,169
Please take these to my desk.

513
00:29:57,253 --> 00:29:58,462
- Okay.
- I'll be right back.

514
00:30:00,298 --> 00:30:01,340
Let's go.

515
00:30:09,598 --> 00:30:10,683
- Hey.
- Hey.

516
00:30:11,517 --> 00:30:12,727
What's up?

517
00:30:13,185 --> 00:30:15,771
Nothing much.

518
00:30:19,150 --> 00:30:21,944
Can I tag along on one of the site visits?

519
00:30:22,445 --> 00:30:23,529
You?

520
00:30:24,530 --> 00:30:25,656
Why?

521
00:30:26,907 --> 00:30:29,785
It'll be a good learning opportunity.

522
00:30:29,869 --> 00:30:31,829
It's also good to meet our producers.

523
00:30:31,912 --> 00:30:34,290
And it's pretty common for lawyers
to go on site visits.

524
00:30:34,373 --> 00:30:35,624
Is that so?

525
00:30:36,542 --> 00:30:39,462
Sure, then. I'll tell Ms. Jung.

526
00:30:39,545 --> 00:30:40,671
You can join her

527
00:30:40,755 --> 00:30:42,089
- and go to Mapo.
- No, Boseong.

528
00:30:43,591 --> 00:30:45,217
I want to go with you.

529
00:30:46,594 --> 00:30:48,095
You'll go to Boseong with me?

530
00:30:49,263 --> 00:30:50,598
Boseong is really far.

531
00:30:50,681 --> 00:30:53,476
And it's an overnight trip. Are you sure?

532
00:30:53,684 --> 00:30:56,562
I know what I'm signing up for.

533
00:30:56,729 --> 00:30:59,440
I have something to ask you there.

534
00:31:01,275 --> 00:31:03,027
Show him you're interested now.

535
00:31:03,110 --> 00:31:04,445
Make him ask you out again.

536
00:31:04,528 --> 00:31:06,280
It's also known to be a great date spot.

537
00:31:07,114 --> 00:31:08,240
Okay.

538
00:31:08,699 --> 00:31:10,785
This was when I realized

539
00:31:12,119 --> 00:31:13,204
Am I asking for too much?

540
00:31:14,413 --> 00:31:17,458
our relationship would begin that day.

541
00:31:18,793 --> 00:31:19,794
No.

542
00:31:20,419 --> 00:31:22,922
You can join us. It's fine.

543
00:31:59,125 --> 00:32:01,252
Alright. I don't look so bad.

544
00:32:05,214 --> 00:32:06,882
Bye.

545
00:32:06,966 --> 00:32:08,759
- Where are you going?
- On a site visit.

546
00:32:08,843 --> 00:32:10,594
- It's an overnight trip.
- Huh?

547
00:32:11,011 --> 00:32:14,723
And if anyone invites you to a wedding,
you should go.

548
00:32:14,807 --> 00:32:15,808
What?

549
00:32:17,143 --> 00:32:18,686
Go to those weddings.

550
00:32:18,853 --> 00:32:20,896
You'll have a chance
to reap the benefits soon.

551
00:32:21,772 --> 00:32:22,940
See you!

552
00:32:23,065 --> 00:32:24,442
What is she talking about?

553
00:32:25,151 --> 00:32:27,194
- Have a good trip!
- Okay!

554
00:32:39,290 --> 00:32:40,708
- Ui-yeong!
- Hey.

555
00:32:40,791 --> 00:32:42,334
- I can take those.
- Thanks.

556
00:32:43,294 --> 00:32:45,588
- Ui-yeong!
- Hey.

557
00:32:46,213 --> 00:32:48,466
I can't believe
I'm going to Boseong again!

558
00:32:48,549 --> 00:32:49,967
Again!

559
00:32:50,050 --> 00:32:52,803
- I don't want to go!
- Come on.

560
00:33:10,821 --> 00:33:12,781
- Aren't you tired?
- I'm fine.

561
00:33:20,122 --> 00:33:21,457
The weather is perfect.

562
00:33:32,885 --> 00:33:35,429
- We've arrived.
- Thanks for driving.

563
00:33:38,557 --> 00:33:40,267
- Hello!
- Hello!

564
00:33:40,351 --> 00:33:42,228
Hello.

565
00:33:42,311 --> 00:33:44,480
Thanks for coming such a long way.

566
00:33:44,563 --> 00:33:47,691
These are some pastries from the hotel.
It's for everyone here.

567
00:33:47,775 --> 00:33:50,319
Oh, my. Thanks so much.

568
00:33:50,402 --> 00:33:52,071
We could have a feast with this!

569
00:33:52,571 --> 00:33:56,075
Since we don't have much time,
you can unpack first

570
00:33:56,158 --> 00:33:57,409
and start your site visit.

571
00:33:57,493 --> 00:33:58,827
- Okay.
- Okay.

572
00:33:58,911 --> 00:34:00,913
- Help him.
- I'm okay.

573
00:34:03,707 --> 00:34:06,877
Don't you think it's odd
that Mr. Kang is here?

574
00:34:07,836 --> 00:34:09,547
Why?

575
00:34:09,630 --> 00:34:11,006
You know.

576
00:34:11,090 --> 00:34:13,259
Why did he come all the way here?

577
00:34:13,509 --> 00:34:15,094
He's carrying all our suitcases, too.

578
00:34:16,762 --> 00:34:18,222
I'm sure he's just here for work.

579
00:34:18,430 --> 00:34:19,932
You may not know it

580
00:34:20,015 --> 00:34:22,142
but it's common for lawyers to go
on site visits.

581
00:34:24,562 --> 00:34:27,022
Why are you defending him?

582
00:34:27,439 --> 00:34:28,732
Something smells fishy.

583
00:34:29,567 --> 00:34:30,568
Hmm?

584
00:34:30,943 --> 00:34:32,278
Must be my perfume.

585
00:34:32,861 --> 00:34:35,823
- Huh? Why are you wearing perfume?
- Just come already!

586
00:34:35,906 --> 00:34:37,157
Ui-yeong!

587
00:34:40,369 --> 00:34:42,746
You can get into two teams for the visit

588
00:34:42,830 --> 00:34:46,333
one for the tea fields
and the other for the factory.

589
00:34:46,500 --> 00:34:48,294
And we can all gather with our crew

590
00:34:48,377 --> 00:34:50,462
- for a dinner together.
- Okay.

591
00:34:50,546 --> 00:34:52,131
How do you want to divide the teams?

592
00:34:52,214 --> 00:34:53,591
I'll go to the fields.

593
00:34:53,674 --> 00:34:57,678
- I'll go to the factory.
- Okay.

594
00:34:57,928 --> 00:34:59,763
I'd also like to go to the fields.

595
00:34:59,888 --> 00:35:01,724
And you're going to the factory, then?

596
00:35:01,807 --> 00:35:03,100
I'd like to go...

597
00:35:04,101 --> 00:35:06,228
to the fields.

598
00:35:06,729 --> 00:35:07,896
Is that okay?

599
00:35:08,647 --> 00:35:10,774
Sure, go ahead.

600
00:35:10,858 --> 00:35:13,068
That's what you're here for, anyway. Go.

601
00:35:13,694 --> 00:35:15,946
- Perfect, let's go.
- Okay!

602
00:35:16,030 --> 00:35:18,699
- Let's get going.
- Okay.

603
00:35:18,782 --> 00:35:20,200
See you later!

604
00:35:20,284 --> 00:35:21,744
Stop it!

605
00:35:21,827 --> 00:35:23,120
Have fun!

606
00:35:29,710 --> 00:35:31,003
Boseong is

607
00:35:31,545 --> 00:35:36,050
oldest tea-producing region
in all of Korea.

608
00:35:36,634 --> 00:35:40,512
CNN selected these lush, green tea fields

609
00:35:40,596 --> 00:35:43,849
as one of the must-see places
around the world.

610
00:35:46,268 --> 00:35:49,647
I bet you feel so peaceful,
looking at the fields every day.

611
00:35:49,730 --> 00:35:50,898
I know, right?

612
00:35:51,190 --> 00:35:54,193
They take such good care of the plants.

613
00:36:00,783 --> 00:36:01,784
Smell it.

614
00:36:04,662 --> 00:36:06,372
Smell it, Sae-byeok.

615
00:36:08,123 --> 00:36:09,792
- Isn't it nice?
- It is!

616
00:36:23,931 --> 00:36:28,227
Planting the tea leaves on a hill
along a zig-zag path

617
00:36:28,310 --> 00:36:30,771
helps the plants get
an even amount of sunlight

618
00:36:30,854 --> 00:36:32,439
- and improve quality.
- It's hot.

619
00:36:32,523 --> 00:36:34,274
The residue from tea production

620
00:36:34,358 --> 00:36:35,859
- Have some water.
- is recycled...

621
00:36:35,943 --> 00:36:37,653
- as fertilizer.
- Thanks.

622
00:36:37,736 --> 00:36:38,987
It's very eco-friendly.

623
00:36:40,030 --> 00:36:41,907
Walking with you

624
00:36:42,241 --> 00:36:44,118
takes me right back to the college days.

625
00:36:44,827 --> 00:36:45,828
You're right.

626
00:36:49,289 --> 00:36:52,084
Ui-yeong, can we talk

627
00:36:53,836 --> 00:36:55,462
just by ourselves later this evening?

628
00:36:56,046 --> 00:36:57,047
What?

629
00:36:59,007 --> 00:37:00,759
Oh, sure.

630
00:37:14,606 --> 00:37:16,316
Oh, gosh.

631
00:37:18,318 --> 00:37:20,779
Everything was great at the factory.

632
00:37:20,863 --> 00:37:22,865
The production process matched
the contract.

633
00:37:22,948 --> 00:37:25,993
They also showed me certifications
of recent hygiene approvals.

634
00:37:27,369 --> 00:37:30,205
The tea fields were also really great.

635
00:37:32,291 --> 00:37:33,459
Hmm?

636
00:37:35,127 --> 00:37:36,962
Define "really great."

637
00:37:37,212 --> 00:37:38,756
Why do you look so in love?

638
00:37:39,798 --> 00:37:42,134
Mr. Kang just sent me some photos he took.

639
00:37:43,427 --> 00:37:45,137
I see.

640
00:37:45,929 --> 00:37:48,223
Men still use the same tricks, huh?

641
00:37:48,474 --> 00:37:50,267
This is a cliché.

642
00:37:50,350 --> 00:37:52,603
Men take photos of everyone

643
00:37:52,686 --> 00:37:55,022
to get a photo of his crush.
That's what he did!

644
00:37:55,939 --> 00:37:58,317
- You think so?
- Yeah!

645
00:38:00,903 --> 00:38:02,112
When did this start?

646
00:38:02,404 --> 00:38:06,366
We don't really talk much
with the Legal Department.

647
00:38:07,743 --> 00:38:11,330
We actually went to college together.

648
00:38:12,080 --> 00:38:13,415
What?

649
00:38:13,832 --> 00:38:15,834
I didn't know you two went way back.

650
00:38:16,251 --> 00:38:18,504
Okay, you've known each other
for long enough.

651
00:38:21,465 --> 00:38:25,135
What would you do

652
00:38:25,302 --> 00:38:26,720
if Mr. Kang asked you out?

653
00:38:27,888 --> 00:38:29,556
Are you okay with dating a coworker?

654
00:38:32,810 --> 00:38:34,812
If that really happens

655
00:38:35,979 --> 00:38:38,023
I'll make sure it doesn't affect our work.

656
00:38:41,610 --> 00:38:44,655
- You're already into him!
- No!

657
00:38:44,738 --> 00:38:45,948
Okay!

658
00:38:46,031 --> 00:38:50,202
I'll just pretend to be sleeping
if you don't come back later.

659
00:38:50,285 --> 00:38:53,372
Why would you put it like that?
We're not there yet!

660
00:38:54,581 --> 00:38:55,749
But you are.

661
00:38:55,833 --> 00:38:57,668
Girls, dinner is ready.

662
00:38:57,751 --> 00:38:59,127
Okay, we'll be right out.

663
00:39:00,838 --> 00:39:03,841
You sure seem excited to go.

664
00:39:03,924 --> 00:39:05,050
Stop it.

665
00:39:06,844 --> 00:39:08,554
- Cheers!
- Good work today.

666
00:39:08,637 --> 00:39:11,223
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

667
00:39:11,306 --> 00:39:15,143
Thank you for all your hard work today.

668
00:39:15,394 --> 00:39:17,229
Ui-yeong, please say something for us.

669
00:39:18,522 --> 00:39:22,568
Thank you so much for letting us have
such a smooth site visit.

670
00:39:22,651 --> 00:39:25,988
We won't let your effort go to waste.
We'll go back and work hard, too.

671
00:39:26,071 --> 00:39:30,659
And please visit our hotel on vacation.
We'll treat you well.

672
00:39:32,286 --> 00:39:34,538
- Let's go!
- Cheers!

673
00:39:34,621 --> 00:39:36,039
- Cheers!
- Yes!

674
00:39:36,123 --> 00:39:37,875
- Great work today.
- Cheers.

675
00:39:37,958 --> 00:39:39,167
Thank you.

676
00:39:39,251 --> 00:39:40,919
- Cheers.
- Thank you.

677
00:39:41,003 --> 00:39:43,005
- Great work.
- Good job.

678
00:39:43,130 --> 00:39:44,756
By the way

679
00:39:44,965 --> 00:39:46,508
I'm not sure if I can ask you this

680
00:39:47,217 --> 00:39:48,302
but are you single?

681
00:39:48,385 --> 00:39:49,636
- Sorry?
- Are you married?

682
00:39:51,430 --> 00:39:53,307
I don't even have a boyfriend.

683
00:39:53,515 --> 00:39:54,933
You're wasting a sunny weekend

684
00:39:55,017 --> 00:39:57,144
with all these old people!

685
00:39:57,227 --> 00:39:59,187
No wonder you don't have one.

686
00:39:59,813 --> 00:40:02,524
It feels like I'm visiting my family.
I love it here.

687
00:40:03,650 --> 00:40:05,527
Even her heart is so beautiful.

688
00:40:05,611 --> 00:40:07,487
- Have some of this.
- Thank you.

689
00:40:07,946 --> 00:40:09,239
Here.

690
00:40:09,907 --> 00:40:12,659
- She has enough!
- Stop it.

691
00:40:12,743 --> 00:40:15,245
- Who cares? We love her.
- My gosh!

692
00:40:15,329 --> 00:40:17,289
You're so funny!

693
00:40:17,372 --> 00:40:18,540
I know.

694
00:40:18,624 --> 00:40:20,083
The food was really good.

695
00:40:20,167 --> 00:40:21,793
- I ate a lot.
- We're out of makgeolli.

696
00:40:21,877 --> 00:40:24,421
- Don't drink so much!
- Okay.

697
00:40:24,504 --> 00:40:25,756
Here you go.

698
00:40:26,423 --> 00:40:27,716
Gosh, I'm so full.

699
00:40:28,592 --> 00:40:31,261
Ui-yeong, you want to take a walk?

700
00:40:31,970 --> 00:40:33,138
Let's do that.

701
00:40:36,975 --> 00:40:38,560
This is nice.

702
00:40:58,205 --> 00:40:59,498
Be careful. Are you alright?

703
00:40:59,623 --> 00:41:01,166
Yeah, I'm fine.

704
00:41:03,251 --> 00:41:04,252
Let's go.

705
00:41:19,142 --> 00:41:20,310
You can sit here.

706
00:41:37,869 --> 00:41:41,373
So, how was the site visit?

707
00:41:43,125 --> 00:41:44,209
It was great.

708
00:41:46,211 --> 00:41:48,672
But I've been too occupied
by something else.

709
00:41:53,802 --> 00:41:55,429
Ui-yeong, I...

710
00:41:57,472 --> 00:41:59,307
didn't come to Boseong for work.

711
00:42:00,308 --> 00:42:01,309
Hmm?

712
00:42:03,020 --> 00:42:04,062
What, then?

713
00:42:07,441 --> 00:42:09,735
I don't know how you'll feel about it

714
00:42:11,069 --> 00:42:14,614
but even after graduating
and when preparing for the bar exam

715
00:42:15,115 --> 00:42:17,075
I still thought about you sometimes.

716
00:42:18,952 --> 00:42:20,037
Me?

717
00:42:20,704 --> 00:42:21,788
Did you?

718
00:42:25,375 --> 00:42:27,502
I wondered who you'd date

719
00:42:28,378 --> 00:42:30,881
and how great he must be.

720
00:42:33,592 --> 00:42:37,137
I had a really hard time getting over it
when you rejected me.

721
00:42:39,222 --> 00:42:40,515
I see.

722
00:42:43,226 --> 00:42:45,520
But thanks to your rejection

723
00:42:45,854 --> 00:42:48,273
I knew where I stood.

724
00:42:49,816 --> 00:42:52,194
So, I studied really hard
and became a lawyer.

725
00:42:52,527 --> 00:42:56,490
To be good enough
for anyone to fall in love with.

726
00:42:57,949 --> 00:43:02,537
Come on. You were already great then.

727
00:43:02,913 --> 00:43:06,875
I just wasn't in a place
for a relationship back then.

728
00:43:07,375 --> 00:43:09,211
No need to be so kind.

729
00:43:10,712 --> 00:43:13,381
I'm over it now.

730
00:43:27,187 --> 00:43:29,439
Remember how I said
I had to ask you something?

731
00:43:31,441 --> 00:43:32,567
Yeah.

732
00:43:34,861 --> 00:43:38,323
How do you feel about workplace dating?

733
00:43:44,496 --> 00:43:47,165
It's not easy, of course.

734
00:43:48,500 --> 00:43:51,545
You're bound to become
the talk of the town at work.

735
00:43:52,629 --> 00:43:55,549
And you'll have to work extra hard.

736
00:43:58,844 --> 00:44:00,137
But...

737
00:44:02,597 --> 00:44:05,016
if you've found someone you like

738
00:44:05,642 --> 00:44:08,854
you should be willing to do that much.

739
00:44:10,397 --> 00:44:13,567
After all, how can you stop yourself
from falling for someone?

740
00:44:15,235 --> 00:44:16,903
Do you really think so?

741
00:44:23,535 --> 00:44:24,703
Okay, Ui-yeong.

742
00:44:26,872 --> 00:44:27,998
Will you...

743
00:44:32,002 --> 00:44:34,754
set me up with Sae-byeok, then?

744
00:44:36,256 --> 00:44:38,633
Hmm? Sae-byeok?

745
00:44:40,260 --> 00:44:41,511
Why Sae-byeok?

746
00:44:41,970 --> 00:44:44,222
I'm going to ask her out tonight.

747
00:44:45,849 --> 00:44:46,933
What?

748
00:44:48,435 --> 00:44:51,229
I rarely get to see her at work.

749
00:44:51,813 --> 00:44:53,231
We work for different departments

750
00:44:53,899 --> 00:44:55,734
and she's an intern.

751
00:44:56,318 --> 00:44:58,904
I've already wasted so many weeks

752
00:45:00,155 --> 00:45:01,781
worrying about how she'd feel.

753
00:45:03,825 --> 00:45:06,119
- Hello.
- You can leave it here.

754
00:45:06,411 --> 00:45:07,913
- Okay.
- Thank you.

755
00:45:18,048 --> 00:45:19,341
- Here.
- Thank you.

756
00:45:19,424 --> 00:45:21,593
Thank you!

757
00:45:41,571 --> 00:45:43,073
I don't want to go!

758
00:45:44,532 --> 00:45:46,743
BOSEONG: UI-YEONG, HYUN-MIN, SAE-BYEOK

759
00:45:48,370 --> 00:45:49,829
Fine.

760
00:45:51,039 --> 00:45:52,082
Check it out.

761
00:45:57,963 --> 00:46:01,258
It's so cute to see her work so hard

762
00:46:02,008 --> 00:46:04,261
but still be so clueless.

763
00:46:06,221 --> 00:46:07,597
I'll head back

764
00:46:08,723 --> 00:46:11,726
and wink at you.

765
00:46:11,851 --> 00:46:15,480
Can you tell Sae-byeok to come here
after a bit?

766
00:46:15,855 --> 00:46:18,692
I'll come here to get ready in advance.

767
00:46:21,569 --> 00:46:23,863
How could he change like this?

768
00:46:25,865 --> 00:46:28,910
If you don't mind, can you bring her here?

769
00:46:31,288 --> 00:46:33,248
Don't stay up too late drinking.

770
00:46:33,331 --> 00:46:34,874
You'll be tired on your way back.

771
00:46:34,958 --> 00:46:37,294
Okay, thank you!

772
00:46:46,011 --> 00:46:50,015
Alright! Why don't we play a game?

773
00:46:50,181 --> 00:46:51,308
Come here, Mr. Kang.

774
00:46:51,683 --> 00:46:53,393
Sae-byeok, join us!

775
00:46:53,476 --> 00:46:54,811
- Let's play a game.
- Okay.

776
00:46:55,603 --> 00:46:57,647
Leave the soju.

777
00:46:58,690 --> 00:47:02,444
Let's play "Truth or Truth."

778
00:47:02,652 --> 00:47:03,903
It's simple.

779
00:47:03,987 --> 00:47:07,782
You can only be truthful
and mean everything you say.

780
00:47:07,866 --> 00:47:09,659
If you insist on staying silent

781
00:47:09,743 --> 00:47:12,203
you can let your liver suffer.

782
00:47:22,172 --> 00:47:23,173
Why...

783
00:47:24,507 --> 00:47:26,259
Why did you come here?

784
00:47:29,637 --> 00:47:31,097
- For work.
- Hey!

785
00:47:31,806 --> 00:47:34,601
Didn't I say you had to be truthful?

786
00:47:34,726 --> 00:47:37,020
This isn't your neighborhood park.

787
00:47:37,103 --> 00:47:38,688
You drove for all those hours

788
00:47:38,772 --> 00:47:40,648
for your crush, didn't you?

789
00:47:40,940 --> 00:47:42,942
Cut it out, Hyun-min.

790
00:47:43,026 --> 00:47:45,487
I got this, okay?

791
00:47:46,488 --> 00:47:48,406
Your crush

792
00:47:48,490 --> 00:47:52,410
no, your dream woman, is here, right?

793
00:47:53,203 --> 00:47:55,705
She has the prettiest face

794
00:47:55,789 --> 00:47:57,874
and is so good at her job.

795
00:47:58,458 --> 00:48:00,251
Isn't it our Ui-yeong?

796
00:48:05,173 --> 00:48:06,216
Sorry?

797
00:48:10,095 --> 00:48:12,472
I've never fallen for anyone like this.

798
00:48:12,555 --> 00:48:15,725
Be my girlfriend!
I promise to make you happy!

799
00:48:17,227 --> 00:48:21,940
Yeah, he definitely said
I was his first love then.

800
00:48:22,816 --> 00:48:26,403
People may change,
but their first loves don't.

801
00:48:26,986 --> 00:48:29,239
Sure, Ui-yeong is great.

802
00:48:30,198 --> 00:48:33,910
But that doesn't mean I want to date her.

803
00:48:34,744 --> 00:48:37,872
She's older. I'm not sure how I feel
about dating someone older than me.

804
00:48:39,207 --> 00:48:40,959
What?

805
00:48:41,543 --> 00:48:43,378
Isn't she only a year older?

806
00:48:43,461 --> 00:48:44,754
When's your birthday?

807
00:48:44,838 --> 00:48:47,882
That's just how I feel.

808
00:48:48,425 --> 00:48:50,260
That's just the case for me.

809
00:48:50,510 --> 00:48:52,470
It's a personal taste. Please respect it.

810
00:48:56,474 --> 00:48:57,642
And...

811
00:49:02,897 --> 00:49:04,774
I have a crush on someone else.

812
00:49:10,947 --> 00:49:12,115
Sae-byeok.

813
00:49:18,580 --> 00:49:20,707
I didn't think I'd ask you out here

814
00:49:24,919 --> 00:49:27,046
but when I look at you

815
00:49:28,923 --> 00:49:31,885
it feels like you make

816
00:49:33,386 --> 00:49:36,097
my forgotten innocence come back.

817
00:49:38,808 --> 00:49:40,059
Will you...

818
00:49:40,977 --> 00:49:42,312
be my girlfriend?

819
00:50:23,853 --> 00:50:25,522
CAUTION SLIPPERY SURFACE

820
00:50:26,814 --> 00:50:28,024
Ui-yeong!

821
00:50:28,233 --> 00:50:30,068
I know it's been ages

822
00:50:30,735 --> 00:50:32,612
but how could you be so wrong?

823
00:50:33,029 --> 00:50:34,489
This is so embarrassing.

824
00:50:35,114 --> 00:50:36,616
Darn it. What a joke.

825
00:50:37,742 --> 00:50:39,369
How do I face them tomorrow?

826
00:50:40,036 --> 00:50:41,996
I know I haven't dated in years

827
00:50:42,080 --> 00:50:43,623
but how can I be so off?

828
00:50:44,707 --> 00:50:47,627
I'm so stupid. And crazy!

829
00:50:57,554 --> 00:50:58,930
Where am I?

830
00:51:54,861 --> 00:51:57,196
- Who's this?
- Please don't kill me!

831
00:52:00,325 --> 00:52:01,743
Ui-yeong?

832
00:52:04,787 --> 00:52:06,706
What are you doing here at this hour?

833
00:52:07,498 --> 00:52:08,708
Hey...

834
00:52:24,557 --> 00:52:28,603
Didn't you see the "Do Not Enter" sign
on your way in?

835
00:52:30,104 --> 00:52:33,358
That's a 30-minute walk from your room.

836
00:52:34,817 --> 00:52:38,321
I just had a lot on my mind,
so I kept walking.

837
00:52:39,447 --> 00:52:42,784
You were so locked in
and just moving forward

838
00:52:42,867 --> 00:52:45,703
that I thought you were
an injured wild animal.

839
00:52:49,707 --> 00:52:52,919
Oh, no. The scar is bad.

840
00:52:53,294 --> 00:52:55,963
Take your time with the tea.
And get some rest.

841
00:52:56,047 --> 00:52:57,507
Let me bring you some ointment.

842
00:52:59,509 --> 00:53:00,677
Keep drinking your tea.

843
00:53:02,929 --> 00:53:04,222
Thank you.

844
00:53:07,850 --> 00:53:09,435
Here.

845
00:53:21,155 --> 00:53:23,491
- By the way
- Yeah?

846
00:53:24,534 --> 00:53:26,160
you let those tea leaves get old

847
00:53:26,994 --> 00:53:29,580
on purpose, right?

848
00:53:31,499 --> 00:53:34,377
Because they get better with time

849
00:53:35,336 --> 00:53:37,088
unlike people.

850
00:53:38,297 --> 00:53:39,507
Right?

851
00:53:43,678 --> 00:53:45,430
You mean these?

852
00:53:46,305 --> 00:53:49,767
I was just too lazy to throw them out.

853
00:53:49,851 --> 00:53:53,396
Half of these are too stale.

854
00:53:55,314 --> 00:53:56,441
Why?

855
00:53:57,567 --> 00:54:01,821
Don't flavors become deeper over time
with tea?

856
00:54:01,904 --> 00:54:05,825
That depends on the tea,
but that's not usually the case.

857
00:54:07,201 --> 00:54:10,455
The fragrance and the flavors become dull.

858
00:54:12,081 --> 00:54:15,960
New leaves grow every year.

859
00:54:16,043 --> 00:54:18,671
What's the point in using stale leaves?

860
00:54:19,338 --> 00:54:21,758
Everything, including tea leaves

861
00:54:21,841 --> 00:54:25,386
lose market value over time.

862
00:54:36,522 --> 00:54:38,733
Lose market value...

863
00:54:40,693 --> 00:54:41,903
over time...

864
00:54:42,695 --> 00:54:45,072
I thought I could find a boyfriend
and fall in love

865
00:54:45,656 --> 00:54:49,243
whenever I decided it was time.

866
00:54:50,244 --> 00:54:52,747
But I had it all wrong.

867
00:54:54,624 --> 00:54:55,833
I've wasted

868
00:54:56,292 --> 00:54:59,879
all my best years for love.

869
00:55:06,427 --> 00:55:07,595
Oh, no.

870
00:55:09,263 --> 00:55:11,849
Hey, Ui-yeong?

871
00:55:14,936 --> 00:55:16,270
Are you crying?

872
00:55:17,355 --> 00:55:18,523
Oh, gosh...

873
00:55:19,690 --> 00:55:22,443
Are you that sad about the tea leaves?

874
00:55:25,238 --> 00:55:26,823
Yeah, it's so sad.

875
00:55:28,032 --> 00:55:30,576
What happens to the old leaves, then?

876
00:55:31,118 --> 00:55:33,287
They thought they'd aged well

877
00:55:33,371 --> 00:55:35,289
only to learn
that they can't make good tea.

878
00:55:36,123 --> 00:55:38,751
Where do they all end up, then?

879
00:55:40,086 --> 00:55:41,420
Oh, goodness.

880
00:55:42,797 --> 00:55:44,048
Gosh...

881
00:55:45,299 --> 00:55:46,467
It's okay.

882
00:55:48,761 --> 00:55:49,887
There, there.

883
00:55:50,972 --> 00:55:52,223
Let it all out.

884
00:55:52,640 --> 00:55:53,891
Cry until you feel better.

885
00:55:55,017 --> 00:55:56,978
Nothing wrong with crying when you're sad.

886
00:55:57,895 --> 00:55:59,188
It's okay.

887
00:55:59,605 --> 00:56:01,065
Let it out.

888
00:56:41,939 --> 00:56:44,066
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

889
00:56:45,526 --> 00:56:47,320
- Enjoy your breakfast.
- Thanks.

890
00:56:50,990 --> 00:56:55,119
The sun is really strong today, huh?

891
00:56:55,202 --> 00:56:57,121
I'd better put on sunscreen.

892
00:56:58,831 --> 00:56:59,916
Gosh.

893
00:57:00,249 --> 00:57:01,542
Enjoy your breakfast.

894
00:57:13,971 --> 00:57:15,139
Ui-yeong!

895
00:57:16,432 --> 00:57:17,934
Weren't you going to help me?

896
00:57:18,017 --> 00:57:19,685
Why did you just leave last night?

897
00:57:20,728 --> 00:57:22,563
I had too much to drink.

898
00:57:24,607 --> 00:57:26,734
Why are you grabbing my wrist?

899
00:57:27,735 --> 00:57:29,111
You're getting too close.

900
00:57:43,668 --> 00:57:46,629
Does he think he hasn't aged?

901
00:57:46,712 --> 00:57:49,131
Dating an older woman sounds hot
when you're 20.

902
00:57:49,215 --> 00:57:50,800
But he's too old for that now.

903
00:57:50,883 --> 00:57:53,552
You know, I didn't believe it

904
00:57:53,803 --> 00:57:56,180
when people said
women were too old past 30.

905
00:57:57,181 --> 00:57:59,892
But I see it now.

906
00:58:02,061 --> 00:58:05,356
They're not saying
women over 30 are worthless.

907
00:58:05,523 --> 00:58:08,693
It's just that women over 30

908
00:58:09,110 --> 00:58:12,071
just get overlooked and forgotten.

909
00:58:12,154 --> 00:58:15,366
Not all people think that way.

910
00:58:15,449 --> 00:58:17,493
I'm fine.

911
00:58:18,786 --> 00:58:22,289
I'm not attracted to a man
who doesn't find older women attractive.

912
00:58:22,373 --> 00:58:25,084
- So?
- But my heart!

913
00:58:25,418 --> 00:58:28,212
My heart just yearned for someone

914
00:58:28,295 --> 00:58:30,965
to think about all the time
and take care of.

915
00:58:31,966 --> 00:58:33,718
Now, it has nowhere to go.

916
00:58:37,013 --> 00:58:40,516
- That's what makes me sad.
- Do-hyun, that jerk.

917
00:58:48,441 --> 00:58:51,277
Why should you have to give up on love

918
00:58:51,360 --> 00:58:53,029
just because he's not attracted to you?

919
00:58:53,112 --> 00:58:54,989
No

920
00:58:56,866 --> 00:58:59,326
- I shouldn't have to give up.
- Just find a new man.

921
00:58:59,410 --> 00:59:00,703
There are dating apps, too.

922
00:59:01,120 --> 00:59:02,663
I hate those.

923
00:59:02,747 --> 00:59:04,790
Okay, go on some blind dates, then.

924
00:59:04,874 --> 00:59:07,460
That's even worse.
It's not romantic at all.

925
00:59:07,543 --> 00:59:10,212
You think men just fall from the sky
like apples do from trees?

926
00:59:10,296 --> 00:59:11,672
You can't just wait for one!

927
00:59:11,756 --> 00:59:15,217
Going on blind dates is
the real organic way of dating.

928
00:59:17,428 --> 00:59:19,764
How's that any organic?

929
00:59:21,057 --> 00:59:24,685
Think about our age, energy,
and the time we have.

930
00:59:25,311 --> 00:59:27,104
Do you have time for book discussions

931
00:59:27,188 --> 00:59:29,023
at a book club after work?

932
00:59:29,315 --> 00:59:31,233
Do you have the energy to stay
at a guesthouse

933
00:59:31,317 --> 00:59:32,943
and party all night?

934
00:59:33,027 --> 00:59:34,612
- I don't.
- See?

935
00:59:34,695 --> 00:59:36,614
Blind dates are organic.

936
00:59:38,407 --> 00:59:41,660
- Oh!
- And blind dates are

937
00:59:41,744 --> 00:59:44,455
for people actively looking for love.

938
00:59:44,538 --> 00:59:48,876
All you have to do is go on one
and see if you're compatible.

939
00:59:48,959 --> 00:59:50,544
How simple is that?

940
00:59:50,628 --> 00:59:53,297
Someone actively looking for love...

941
00:59:57,510 --> 00:59:59,887
- I'll go on one.
- Yes, do it.

942
01:00:00,930 --> 01:00:02,473
I'll go on blind dates, alright!

943
01:00:02,556 --> 01:00:04,100
Okay, let's go!

944
01:00:04,183 --> 01:00:05,434
Right on.

945
01:00:11,524 --> 01:00:12,900
- Hello.
- Hello.

946
01:00:13,234 --> 01:00:15,361
- Hello.
- Check the kitchen.

947
01:00:15,444 --> 01:00:16,487
Yes, sir.

948
01:00:16,570 --> 01:00:17,947
- Hello.
- Hello.

949
01:00:18,906 --> 01:00:21,117
- Mr. Eun! I'll do it!
- Oh, gosh.

950
01:00:22,076 --> 01:00:23,536
Do what?

951
01:00:25,329 --> 01:00:28,332
Go on the blind date you mentioned.

952
01:00:28,791 --> 01:00:30,209
Is he still single?

953
01:00:38,843 --> 01:00:41,178
And that's how I ended up here.

954
01:01:02,324 --> 01:01:05,578
I had to do some last-minute studying
for this unexpected date.

955
01:01:05,661 --> 01:01:08,122
That's how you casually start
a conversation.

956
01:01:08,414 --> 01:01:10,833
You can also talk
about the one who set you up.

957
01:01:10,916 --> 01:01:15,379
Remember to talk
about what you have in common.

958
01:01:15,546 --> 01:01:17,715
That'll make you feel closer to your date.

959
01:01:21,719 --> 01:01:23,971
I hear you know Mr. Eun

960
01:01:24,430 --> 01:01:27,183
from volunteering
at a dog shelter together.

961
01:01:27,516 --> 01:01:30,895
I hear you walk dogs for almost 10km.

962
01:01:30,978 --> 01:01:33,689
Oh, I just really love dogs

963
01:01:33,772 --> 01:01:35,774
but can't have one because I'm allergic.

964
01:01:36,025 --> 01:01:37,985
It's good exercise for me, too.
I enjoy it.

965
01:01:40,196 --> 01:01:42,615
Do you have some photos of the dogs?

966
01:01:44,617 --> 01:01:45,743
Here.

967
01:01:46,327 --> 01:01:47,703
That's adorable!

968
01:01:48,370 --> 01:01:49,455
It's a pup.

969
01:01:50,206 --> 01:01:52,082
I also really love dogs.

970
01:01:53,000 --> 01:01:57,129
If you also love dogs,
you should volunteer with me sometime.

971
01:01:58,088 --> 01:01:59,173
"Sometime"?

972
01:02:02,343 --> 01:02:05,554
Did he just ask me out on a second date?

973
01:02:20,361 --> 01:02:23,072
Do you live with your parents?

974
01:02:23,739 --> 01:02:27,618
No, I've been living alone for a while.

975
01:02:29,495 --> 01:02:31,789
I still live with my mom

976
01:02:31,872 --> 01:02:34,041
so I'm so curious about living alone.
How is it?

977
01:02:35,167 --> 01:02:38,087
It's easy. You do the laundry and clean
whenever you want.

978
01:02:38,295 --> 01:02:39,797
You can also sleep all you want.

979
01:02:41,131 --> 01:02:43,133
But living with your family is
better sometimes

980
01:02:43,217 --> 01:02:45,511
even if it can be inconvenient.

981
01:02:45,678 --> 01:02:48,347
Food tastes better
when you eat with people.

982
01:02:48,597 --> 01:02:52,142
Living alone means
I just rush through my meals.

983
01:02:52,226 --> 01:02:53,519
Really?

984
01:02:53,727 --> 01:02:57,189
You need to take better care of yourself
since you live alone.

985
01:02:57,898 --> 01:03:00,276
You need to check on how you're feeling

986
01:03:00,776 --> 01:03:03,070
and eat better meals.

987
01:03:04,863 --> 01:03:06,573
Okay, I'll do that.

988
01:03:07,825 --> 01:03:12,830
By the way, dating someone might mean
you won't be as focused on your career.

989
01:03:12,997 --> 01:03:14,707
Are you okay with that?

990
01:03:16,083 --> 01:03:18,002
A relationship that affects my work...

991
01:03:19,837 --> 01:03:21,880
I'd love a relationship like that.

992
01:03:22,798 --> 01:03:25,092
That'd mean
that the person matters to me that much.

993
01:03:28,470 --> 01:03:31,807
I have one more question for you.

994
01:03:32,891 --> 01:03:36,312
He has so many questions
because he's curious about me, right?

995
01:03:36,729 --> 01:03:38,439
This is going so well.

996
01:03:39,148 --> 01:03:41,025
Sure, ask away.

997
01:03:42,443 --> 01:03:44,570
My blood type is O,
and my personality type ENFP.

998
01:03:44,653 --> 01:03:46,572
I'm a Cancer,
an early bird, and a homebody.

999
01:03:46,655 --> 01:03:48,782
- Winter is my favorite season.
- Ui-yeong

1000
01:03:49,199 --> 01:03:54,246
how do you feel
about dating me with marriage in mind?

1001
01:03:57,833 --> 01:04:01,462
Did you just say "marriage"?

1002
01:04:01,837 --> 01:04:04,048
Yeah, I want to date

1003
01:04:05,341 --> 01:04:06,717
to get married.

1004
01:04:09,553 --> 01:04:11,180
"Going so well," my ass.

1005
01:04:12,890 --> 01:04:14,183
It's a blind date.

1006
01:04:16,477 --> 01:04:17,728
It's the real deal.

1007
01:04:33,660 --> 01:04:35,996
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

1008
01:04:41,627 --> 01:04:43,712
I'M HIS FIRST LOVE

1009
01:04:48,592 --> 01:04:51,178
YOU'RE BEAUTIFUL, THEN AND NOW

1010
01:04:51,678 --> 01:04:54,264
OR CHAMPAGNE FOR ROMANCE?

1011
01:05:02,106 --> 01:05:04,233
LOVE THAT DISTRACTS YOU FROM YOUR CAREER

1012
01:05:08,737 --> 01:05:10,739
My blind date's car is...

1013
01:05:12,366 --> 01:05:14,368
It was, like, a white dolphin?

1014
01:05:14,451 --> 01:05:16,995
I just happened to find out
that my blind date had an expensive car.

1015
01:05:17,079 --> 01:05:18,872
He still hasn't asked you out
on a second date?

1016
01:05:18,956 --> 01:05:21,583
You can see her next week,
but you still have to ask her out soon.

1017
01:05:21,959 --> 01:05:23,252
My phone...

1018
01:05:23,961 --> 01:05:25,212
He still hasn't texted me.

1019
01:05:25,295 --> 01:05:28,841
You want me to set you up
with a really great guy?

1020
01:05:30,342 --> 01:05:32,302
Your ex? Your ex-ex-boyfriend?

1021
01:05:32,845 --> 01:05:34,179
You're going to crawl to the exit?

1022
01:05:35,055 --> 01:05:36,056
Ui-yeong?

1023
01:05:36,140 --> 01:05:37,599
I can't help but keep imagining

1024
01:05:37,850 --> 01:05:41,979
what it'd be like to leave my life
in his hands.

1025
01:05:42,354 --> 01:05:44,815
It'd probably be
even better than I imagine.

1026
01:05:50,863 --> 01:05:52,865
Subtitles by: Min-sun Kim
